The paper focuses on software testing and mutation analysis, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of tailored mutation operators involves modifying the codebase, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). The evaluation of the approach is based on the Defects4J dataset, which is a well-known dataset for software debugging (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of mutation analysis, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CR).
